From Doug Zolmer Subject Re Honda clutch chatter In article James Bruder writes anyone else experiencing a similar problem This concerns the clutch on a Honda Accord When the clutch is first used in the morning about the first miles of shifting there is a significant amount of clutch chatter until things warm Then the clutch shifts This chatter started when I moved to the San Francisco Bay area from a low humidity The dealer stated that this is known to happen since Honda changed from an asbestos to non asbestos clutch No remedy Seems that moisture on clutch surface causes slipping until the moisture Any comments out there The clutch on my ' Honda Civic EX V EX in the does this It's Now that I think about it is worse when the humidity is The dealer also claims there's nothing they can do since the clutch is a self adjusting hydraulic design Yeah Doug Zolmer Internet Disclaimer My opinions only Bell Northern Research Ottawa Ontario Canada Service Control Point Routing Services Design Conform Moooo